'''Amélie Gillette ''' is an American newspaper columnist and television writer. She wrote the weekly infographic "The Tolerability Index"<ref name="tolerability" /> for ''[[The A.V. Club]]'' for 10 years and was a writer for the US version of ''[[The Office (U.S. TV series)|The Office]]''.<ref name="imdb" /> She has written for many publications, including ''[[Spin (magazine)|Spin]]'',<ref>{{cite web|last=Gillette |first=Amelie |url=https://www.spin.com/2005/07/clothes-make-maniacs/ |title=Clothes Make the Maniacs &#124; SPIN &#124; Profiles &#124; Spotlight |publisher=SPIN |date=2005-07-11 |accessdate=2013-04-27}}</ref> ''[[The Believer (magazine)|The Believer]]'',<ref>{{cite web|author=U.S.A. |url=http://www.believermag.com/issues/201002/?read=article_gillette |title=The Believer – Becoming a Lady |publisher=Believermag.com |date= |accessdate=2013-04-27}}</ref> and ''[[Blender (magazine)|Blender]]''.<ref name="Gothamist">{{cite web |last=Parker |first=Billy |url=http://gothamist.com/2009/08/17/amelie_gillette_hater.php |title=Amelie Gillette, The Onion's "Hater" |publisher=Gothamist |date=2009-08-17 |accessdate=2013-04-27 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141229024949/http://gothamist.com/2009/08/17/amelie_gillette_hater.php |archivedate=2014-12-29 |df= }}</ref>
== Early life == Gillette is from [[New Orleans]], [[Louisiana]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.zulkey.com/2010/03/the_amelie_gillette_interview.php |title=Zulkey.com |publisher=Zulkey.com |date=2010-03-19 |accessdate=2013-04-27}}</ref> She attended [[New York University]], where she wrote for ''[[Washington Square News]]''.<ref name="Gothamist" /> After graduation, she worked as a freelance writer and taught English in Italy.<ref name="Gothamist" />
== ''The A.V. Club'' (2006–present) == Gillette began writing for ''The Onion''{{'}}s entertainment newspaper ''[[The A.V. Club]]'' in 2006. She wrote "The Hater" column and "The Tolerability Index" infographic, and was the featured performer of The Hater podcast. The last Hater column was published in 2010,<ref>{{cite web|last=Gillette |first=Amelie |url=http://www.avclub.com/articles/this-has-been-the-hater,40772/ |title=This Has Been The Hater &#124; TV &#124; Hater |publisher=The A.V. Club |date=2010-05-06 |accessdate=2013-04-27}}</ref> but she continued to write "The Tolerability Index" until 2016.<ref name="tolerability">{{cite web|url=http://www.avclub.com/features/tolerability-index/ |title=Tolerability Index |publisher=The A.V. Club |date= |accessdate=2013-04-27}}</ref><ref>http://www.avclub.com/article/week-were-barely-putting-end-tolerability-index-234825</ref> She has also written headlines for ''The Onion''.<ref name="Gothamist" />
== Television writing (2010–present) == Gillette joined the writing staff of ''The Office'' beginning in its [[The Office (U.S. season 7)|seventh season]].<ref name="imdb">https://www.imdb.com/name/nm4338665/</ref> She had met ''Office'' cast member [[Ellie Kemper]] a few times prior to joining ''The Office'' writing staff, since Kemper was a writer for ''The Onion'' and ''[[McSweeney's]]''.<ref>{{cite web|last=Miller |first=Julie |url=http://www.movieline.com/2010/08/ellie-kemper-on-being-the-next-mindy-kaling-and-steve-carells-office-replacement.php |title=Ellie Kemper on Being the 'Next Mindy Kaling' and Steve Carell's Office Replacement |publisher=Movieline |date=2010-08-05 |accessdate=2013-04-27}}</ref> She joined the staff of the [[NBC]] sitcom ''[[Animal Practice]]'' in 2012; however, the show was cancelled before her credited episode, "Wingmen," aired. The episode later appeared in a Spring 2013 "burn off."
