{{Infobox venue | name = Florida Studio Theatre | nickname = | former names = | image = Florida Studio Theatre, The Hegner Theatre Wing.png | image_size = | image_alt = | caption = | address = 1241 North Palm Avenue | location = [[Sarasota, Florida]] | coordinates = <!-- {{Coord|LAT|LON|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} --> | type = [[Theatre]] | broke_ground = | built = | opened = {{start date|1973}} | renovated = | expanded = | owner = | operator = | production = | cost = | architect = | builder = | capacity = | acreage = | embedded = | website = {{URL|floridastudiotheatre.org}} | publictransit = [[Sarasota County Area Transit]] }}
The '''Florida Studio Theatre''' or '''FST''' is a [[nonprofit organization|non-profit]] [[theatre]] located in [[Sarasota, Florida|Sarasota]], [[Florida]] at 1241 North Palm Avenue.<ref name="autogenerated1">"Florida Studio Theatre." Florida Studio Theatre. Florida Studio Theatre, n.d. Web. 31 Dec. 2012.</ref> FST produces contemporary plays with over 32,000 subscribers a year. It has been in operation since 1973 and currently serves over 200,000 attendees per year. Its major programs include the Mainstage Series, the Cabaret Series, Stage III, New Play Development, Education, and Write A Play.<ref>"Arts List." HeraldTribune.com. N.p., n.d. Web. 20 Dec. 2012.</ref>
