"'''Jerusalem'''" is a [[song]] by [[Dan Bern]], appearing on his 1996 album, ''Dan Bern''.<ref name="amazon">{{cite web|title=Jerusalem|url=https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B00138GFBG/ref=dm_mu_dp_trk1|publisher=[[Amazon.com]]|accessdate=7 January 2014}}</ref> <ref name="apple">{{cite web|title=Dan Bern|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/dan-bern/id190370131| work=[[iTunes]]|publisher=[[Apple Inc.]]|accessdate=7 January 2014}}</ref> <ref name="allmusic">{{cite web|title=Jerusalem|url=http://www.allmusic.com/song/jerusalem-mt0006259054|publisher=allmusic.com|accessdate=7 January 2014}}</ref> <ref name="youtube">{{cite web|title=Dan Bern – Jerusalem|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xAGKdkf0viM|publisher=[[YouTube]]|accessdate=7 January 2014}}</ref> At the end of the song the singer reveals that he is the [[messiah]]. The song opens and closes with the lyrics "''When I tell you that I love you don't test my love / Accept my love / Don't test my love / 'Cuz maybe I don't love you all that much''."<ref>{{cite web| url=http://danbern.redacorn.net/lyrics/jerusalem.html | title=Dan Bern – Jerusalem: Song Lyrics | website=The Dan Bern Lyrics Archive | accessdate=25 October 2015 }}</ref>

This song has been covered by folk singer-songwriter [[Ani DiFranco]]. It has been featured in the weather section of the podcast ''[[Welcome to Night Vale]]''.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://podbay.fm/show/536258179/e/1345032000 | title=Welcome to Night Vale | website=Podbay.fm | accessdate=25 October 2015 }}</ref>

