{{unreliable sources|date=June 2017}} {{Spanish name|Calzadilla|Bichara}} {{Infobox person | name = Sofía Álvarez | image = | caption = | birth_name = Sofía Calzadilla Bichara | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1958|4|29}} | birth_place = [[Mexico]] | residence= | relatives = [[Sofía Álvarez (actress, born 1913)|Sofía Álvarez]] (grandmother) | years_active = 1963–present | spouse = [[Héctor Bonilla]] (1985-present) | children = Fernando Bonilla Álvarez | occupation = Actress, Voice Actress, Singer, Writer, Producer }}
'''Sofía Álvarez''' (born '''Sofía Calzadilla Bichara''' on April 29, 1958 in [[Mexico]]) is a [[Mexican people|Mexican]] [[actress]] and writer. She is known better for ''Contando con Sofía'' (1978), ''Sofiando'' (1984) and ''Ladies Night'' (2003).
== Biography == Álvarez was born in April 29, 1958 in [[Mexico]]. Her debut career started in 1963 at 5 years old, dubbing several films like The third secret. She also lent her voice to several television series. In 1978, she joined Canal 11 in Mexico, where she presented the program ''Cuenta con Sofía'', showing her ease in inventing children's stories. In 1979 she played in the film ''Maria de mi corazón'' in which she met [[Héctor Bonilla]] and the director Jaime Humberto Hermosillo.
Animated by [[Héctor Bonilla]], Sofia switched to the television Televisa, in which both shared credits in the telenovela ''[[Atrapada]]'', at the end of this production in 1992, Bonilla is vetoed from the television station and next to Sofía are again integrated into the ranks of TvAzteca. In 1994, Sophia starred in the episode "Andamos brujas" of the series of television ''Entre vivos y muertos''. In 2003 she appeared in the film ''Ladies night''. In 2005 she appeared to the cast of the telenovela ''La otra mitad del sol''.
In 2014 she appeared in the cast telenovela ''Amor sin reserva'' and in 2015 played in the film ''Refugio''.
== Personal life == Álvarez married [[Héctor Bonilla]] in 1985 and in the same same year gave birth to her only son Fernando.
