'''''The Heirs of Anthony Boucher''''' is a book written by Marvin Lachman<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://trove.nla.gov.au/work/201853331?q&versionId=221651915|title=The heirs of Anthony Boucher [electronic resource] : a history of mystery fandom / by Marvin Lachman. - Version details|website=Trove|language=en|access-date=2017-03-22}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.abebooks.com/servlet/BookDetailsPL?bi=13530249380&searchurl=&cmtrack_data=cm_abecat=100202094|title=The Heirs of Anthony Boucher (Paperback) by Marvin Lachman: Poisoned Pen Press, United States 9781590582237 Paperback - The Book Depository|website=www.abebooks.com|language=en|access-date=2017-03-22}}</ref> and published by [[Poisoned Pen Press]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://poisonedpenpress.com/books/the-heirs-of-anthony-boucher/|title=The Heirs of Anthony Boucher - Poisoned Pen Press|work=Poisoned Pen Press|access-date=2017-03-22|language=en-US}}</ref> on 1 August 2005, which later went on to win the [[Anthony Award]] for Best Critical Nonfiction in 2006.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.bouchercon.com/anthony-awards/winners-and-nominees/2000s/|title=Winners and Nominees 2000s|date=2015-09-22|work=Bouchercon|access-date=2017-03-22|language=en}}</ref>
